-- SAC Adds to News Corp., EBay Stakes in Fourth Quarter
-- B y   S a i j e l   K i s h a n
-- 2013-02-15T00:02:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-15/sac-adds-to-news-corp-ebay-stakes-in-fourth-quarter.html
SAC Capital Advisors LP, the $14
billion hedge fund run by  Steven A. Cohen , boosted its stakes in
News Corp., EBay Inc. and Facebook Inc. in the fourth quarter.  The fund bought 5.9 million shares of News Corp., bringing
its stake to 9.57 million shares as of Dec. 31, according to a
filing today with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.
SAC added 2.06 million shares of San Jose, California-based
EBay, bringing its stake in the operator of the world’s largest
online marketplace to 4.58 million shares. News Corp and EBay
are SAC’s second-largest and third-largest holdings
respectively.  SAC bought 8 million shares of Facebook, operator of the
world’s largest social network, bringing its stake to 8.5
million shares, according to the filing.  Jonathan Gasthalter , a spokesman for Stamford, Connecticut-
based SAC Capital, declined to comment.  For Related News and Information:  To contact the reporter on this story:
